# Project stack — AI Devs vol. 4

This repository contains course tasks for **AI Devs 4** and consumes the **Cursor Collections** (Eversis) framework via the git submodule **[`third-party/github-collections`](/third-party/github-collections)** — symlinked `.cursor/prompts`, `.cursor/skills`, and shared rules. The authoritative framework doc is **[`third-party/github-collections/documentation/cursor-collection.md`](/third-party/github-collections/third-party/github-collections/documentation/cursor-collection.md)** (also reachable as **[`documentation/cursor-collection.md`](/third-party/github-collections/documentation/cursor-collection.md)**); the workflow entry point is **[`AGENTS.md`](/third-party/github-collections/AGENTS.md)**.

| Area                   | This repository                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
| ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Product**            | Educational AI agent tasks — one subfolder per episode (`tasks/sXXeYY/`)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |
| **Runtime**            | **Bun** — use `bun` for all execution, testing, and package management. See the `use-bun-instead-of-node-vite-npm-pnpm` rule for the full list of Bun APIs to prefer.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        |
| **Language**           | TypeScript (ESNext, strict, bundler module resolution, `noEmit: true`)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |
| **Agent architecture** | ReAct loop, MCP-based tools, Observer/Reflector memory — see [tasks/docs/boilerplate-documentation.md](/tasks/docs/boilerplate-documentation.md)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
| **Agent runtime**      | **`tasks/boilerplate/`** (`@ai-devs/agent-boilerplate`) — canonical agent runtime package: ReAct loop, AIAdapter (retry/backoff), MCP client/server, native tools, logger, memory scaffold. Consume via `"@ai-devs/agent-boilerplate": "file:../boilerplate"` in task `package.json`. See [tasks/boilerplate/README.md](/tasks/boilerplate/README.md) and [tasks/docs/boilerplate-documentation.md](/tasks/docs/boilerplate-documentation.md). |
| **Shared code**        | `tasks/shared/` — domain-specific helpers (e.g. `fetchPeople`, `filterPeople`); distinct from the agent runtime in `tasks/boilerplate/`.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |
| **Prompts**            | `.cursor/prompts/public/` and `internal/` (`eversis-*.md`); attach with **`@eversis-*`** in Chat or Agent                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    |
| **Skills**             | `.cursor/skills/eversis-*/` — list and read via `eversis-collections` MCP server (`eversis_skills_list`, `eversis_skills_get`)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |

## Task structure

Each task lives in `tasks/sXXeYY/` and follows this layout:

```text
tasks/sXXeYY/
├── index.ts          # Entrypoint (bootstrap)
├── src/
│   ├── agent/        # agent.ts, ai.ts, memory.ts
│   ├── mcp/          # client.ts, server.ts
│   ├── tools/        # native/ and mcp/
│   ├── prompts/      # *.md system prompts
│   └── types/        # index.ts (Zod schemas + interfaces)
├── package.json
└── tsconfig.json
```

New tasks must follow the architecture described in [tasks/docs/boilerplate-documentation.md](/tasks/docs/boilerplate-documentation.md).

### Boilerplate package quality commands

Run from **`tasks/boilerplate/`** when editing the shared runtime:

- **Tests:** `bun test`
- **Type-check:** `bunx tsc --noEmit`
- **Install deps:** `bun install`

## Quality commands

Run from the task directory (`tasks/sXXeYY/`):

- **Run task:** `bun --env-file=../.env run index.ts`
- **Tests:** `bun test`
- **Type-check:** `bunx tsc --noEmit` (or use Bun's built-in TS support)
- **Install deps:** `bun install`

## Conventions

- Use `zod` for all schema definitions and tool input validation.
- Store all long prompt strings in `src/prompts/*.md`; load with `fs.readFileSync`. Never hardcode multi-line prompts in TS files.
- MCP tools must return `{ content: [{ type: "text", text: string }] }`.
- Use the `logger.ts` pattern (`[MYŚL]`, `[AKCJA]`, `[WYNIK]`, `[SYSTEM]`) for agent loop output.
- `MAX_ITERATIONS` guard is required in every agent loop.
- Retry / exponential backoff is required for all HTTP calls to course APIs (HTTP 503 is expected).
